00:00:06.900 --> 00:00:09.500
Honey-Chocolate Cake with Spices

00:00:09.500 --> 00:00:11.200
Serves: 8

00:00:11.200 --> 00:00:12.300
Ingredients

00:00:12.300 --> 00:00:17.300
175 g dark chocolate, roughly chopped

00:00:17.300 --> 00:00:21.800
175 g (¾ cup) caster sugar

00:00:21.800 --> 00:00:27.200
125 g (½ cup) butter, cut into cubes

00:00:27.200 --> 00:00:33.800
175 g (1¼ cups) flour + 4 tbsp Extra

00:00:33.800 --> 00:00:35.100
4 eggs

00:00:35.100 --> 00:00:37.400
½ tsp baking powder

00:00:37.400 --> 00:00:39.400
2 tsp clear honey

00:00:39.400 --> 00:00:42.000
2 tsp vanilla powder

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:44.000
2 tsp cinnamon

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:46.000
1 tsp nutmeg

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:47.300
Directions

00:00:47.300 --> 00:00:53.000
Preheat the oven to 150°C and line the cake mould with parchment paper

00:00:53.000 --> 00:01:00.000
In a large bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:02.500
and whisk together to combine

00:01:02.500 --> 00:01:05.200
Break the chocolate into small pieces and melt over a bain-marie

00:01:05.200 --> 00:01:12.200
In a separate bowl, whisk the eggs and sugar until pale and foamy

00:01:12.200 --> 00:01:27.500
When the chocolate is melted, stir in the cubes of butter one by one then the honey

00:01:27.500 --> 00:01:34.200
then pour the mixture onto the egg-sugar mixture and stir until perfectly combined

00:01:34.200 --> 00:01:43.200
Gradually add the dry ingredients and gently fold using a rubber spatula

00:01:43.200 --> 00:01:51.000
Pour the mixture into the mould and bake in the preheated oven for 40-45 minutes

00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:55.000
Leave cooling completely before serving

